snippet: Islamic State militants are still dominating the fight in Iraq’s crucial Anbar Province weeks into the American air campaign.
abstract: Islamic State militants are still dominating fight in Iraq’s crucial Anbar Province weeks into American air campaign, with Iraqi military unable to make most of coalition air support; air campaign has been limited in Anbar, in part because Iraqi forces there have mostly stayed at their garrisons despite American for them to leave their bases and seize initiative.

byline.original: By KIRK SEMPLE and ERIC SCHMITT
byline.contributor: Kirk Semple reported from Baghdad, and Eric Schmitt from Washington.

lead_paragraph: Islamic State militants are still dominating the fight in Iraq’s crucial Anbar Province weeks into the American air campaign.

headline.main: ISIS Keeps Up Pressure Near Baghdad as Iraqi Troops Hesitate
